Executive Profile
Brian J. Stief  Chief Financial Officer and Executive Vice President, Johnson Controls International plcAgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 1 Board Members in 1 different organizations across 1 different industries.61$5,867,700As of Fiscal Year 2016
Background

		Mr. Brian J. Stief has been the Chief Financial Officer and Executive Vice President of Johnson Controls International plc (formerly, Johnson Controls Inc.) since September 2014. Mr. Stief served as Vice President and Corporate Controller of Johnson Controls International plc. since July 2010 until September 2014. He was responsible for global finance functions, financial planning and analysis and corporate taxation. He works closely with Johnson Controls' business units, ... providing support to those senior leadership teams on strategic initiatives, including merger and acquisition opportunities. Prior to joining Johnson Controls, Mr. Stief was a Partner of PricewaterhouseCoopers, which he joined in 1979 and was admitted to the partnership in 1989. During his career at PricewaterhouseCoopers, he primarily served its largest clients such as Caterpillar Inc., Johnson Controls and SABMiller and also held various office managing partner roles. He has been a Director of Johnson Controls Inc., since September 2016. Over the years, he has been an active Member in the Milwaukee community, serving on the Board of Directors of the United Performing Arts Fund, the Junior Achievement Board of Directors, the U.S. Bank Championship Board of Directors and the Greater Milwaukee Committee. A graduate of the University of Iowa, Mr. Stief holds a Bachelor's of Business Administration in Finance and Accounting from the same university.Read Full Background




